%%{init: {'theme':'base'}}%%
usecaseDiagram
actor Student as S
actor Instructor as I
actor SystemAdministrator as A
actor System as SYS

S --> (Register / Login)
S --> (View Courses)
S --> (Enroll in Section)
S --> (Start Quiz)
S --> (Use PowerUp)
S --> (Submit Attempt)
S --> (View Leaderboard)
S --> (View Badges & XP)

I --> (Login)
I --> (Create Quiz)
I --> (Edit Quiz)
I --> (Publish Quiz)
I --> (View Pending Attempts)
I --> (Grade Attempt)
I --> (View Analytics)
I --> (View Instructor Leaderboard)

A --> (Create Users)
A --> (Create Courses)
A --> (Create Sections)
A --> (Assign Instructors)
A --> (Seed Demo Data)
A --> (View System Logs)

(Submit Attempt) ..> (Auto-grade MCQs) : <<include>>
(Grade Attempt) ..> (Update XP & Badges) : <<include>>
(Auto-grade MCQs) ..> SYS
(Update XP & Badges) ..> SYS
(Use PowerUp) ..> SYS

%% Grouping: system-level responsibilities
rect rgb(240,240,255)
  (Auto-grade MCQs)
  (Update XP & Badges)
  (Unlock PowerUps & Badges)
end

(Grade Attempt) ..> (Unlock PowerUps & Badges) : <<include>>
(Unlock PowerUps & Badges) ..> SYS

%% Notes
note right of I
  Instructor monitors:
  - pending attempts
  - analytics
  - leaderboards
end

note right of A
  Setup / maintenance role:
  - bootstrap users, courses, sections
  - inspect logs
  - keep the system ready for instructors and students
end
